===Etymology===
<div style="float:right">
{{wp|ja:キリ}}
{{wp|Paulownia tomentosa}}
</div>
{{ja-kanjitab|きり|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=きり|-}}.  The tree may have been imported from China prior to the {{w|Nara period}}.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2}}</ref>

The term might be from {{m|ja|切り|tr=kiri||cutting}}, from the way that the tree is quick to send out shoots after being cut.<ref name="NJ">[http://www.nihonjiten.com/data/46252.html 桐 at ''Nihon Jiten''] (in Japanese)</ref>

Some sources<ref name="NJ"/> also speculate that this might be from some term {{m|ja|木理|tr=*kiri||wood grain}} in reference to the desirable grain of this wood.  However, {{m|ja|木理}} is only attested with the reading ''mokuri'', not ''kiri''; also, the term is not attested until the 1830s, before which the Japanese terms for {{m|en|[[wood]] [[grain]]}} were {{m|ja|木目|tr=mokume|pos=from the mid-1500s}} or {{m|ja|木目|tr=kime|pos=from the 1200s}}.

